service:
Welcome to the AWS Amplify API documentation. This reference provides descriptions of the actions and data types for the Amplify API.

Amplify enables developers to develop and deploy cloud-powered mobile and web apps. The Amplify Console provides a continuous delivery and hosting service for web applications. For more information, see the Amplify Console User Guide. The Amplify Framework is a comprehensive set of SDKs, libraries, tools, and documentation for client app development. For more information, see the Amplify Framework.

operations.CreateBackendEnvironment: Creates a new backend environment for an Amplify app.
operations.CreateBranch: Creates a new branch for an Amplify app.
operations.CreateDeployment: Creates a deployment for a manually deployed Amplify app. Manually deployed apps are not connected to a repository.
operations.CreateDomainAssociation: Creates a new domain association for an Amplify app. This action associates a custom domain with the Amplify app
operations.CreateWebhook: Creates a new webhook on an Amplify app.
operations.DeleteApp: Deletes an existing Amplify app specified by an app ID.
operations.DeleteBackendEnvironment: Deletes a backend environment for an Amplify app.
operations.DeleteBranch: Deletes a branch for an Amplify app.
operations.DeleteDomainAssociation: Deletes a domain association for an Amplify app.
operations.DeleteJob: Deletes a job for a branch of an Amplify app.
operations.GenerateAccessLogs: Returns the website access logs for a specific time range using a presigned URL.
operations.GetApp: Returns an existing Amplify app by appID.
operations.GetArtifactUrl: Returns the artifact info that corresponds to an artifact id.
operations.GetBackendEnvironment: Returns a backend environment for an Amplify app.
operations.GetBranch: Returns a branch for an Amplify app.
operations.GetDomainAssociation: Returns the domain information for an Amplify app.
operations.GetJob: Returns a job for a branch of an Amplify app.
operations.GetWebhook: Returns the webhook information that corresponds to a specified webhook ID.
operations.ListApps: Returns a list of the existing Amplify apps.
operations.ListArtifacts: Returns a list of artifacts for a specified app, branch, and job.
operations.ListBackendEnvironments: Lists the backend environments for an Amplify app.
operations.ListBranches: Lists the branches of an Amplify app.
operations.ListDomainAssociations: Returns the domain associations for an Amplify app.
operations.ListJobs: Lists the jobs for a branch of an Amplify app.
operations.ListTagsForResource: Returns a list of tags for a specified Amazon Resource Name (ARN).
operations.ListWebhooks: Returns a list of webhooks for an Amplify app.
operations.StartDeployment: Starts a deployment for a manually deployed app. Manually deployed apps are not connected to a repository.
operations.StartJob: Starts a new job for a branch of an Amplify app.
operations.StopJob: Stops a job that is in progress for a branch of an Amplify app.
operations.TagResource: Tags the resource with a tag key and value.
operations.UntagResource: Untags a resource with a specified Amazon Resource Name (ARN).
operations.UpdateBranch: Updates a branch for an Amplify app.
operations.UpdateDomainAssociation: Creates a new domain association for an Amplify app.

JobSummary.base: Describes the summary for an execution job for an Amplify app.

refs.JobSummary$jobType: The type for the job. If the value is RELEASE, the job was manually released from its source by using the StartJob API. If the value is RETRY, the job was manually retried using the StartJob API. If the value is WEB_HOOK, the job was automatically triggered by webhooks.
refs.StartJobRequest$jobType: Describes the type for the job. The job type RELEASE starts a new job with the latest change from the specified branch. This value is available only for apps that are connected to a repository. The job type RETRY retries an existing job. If the job type value is RETRY, the jobId is also required.
